58.0	Terry_Riley	Terry Riley	Terrence Mitchell Riley, (born June 24, 1935) is an American composer intrinsically associated with the minimalist school of Western classical music and was a pioneer of the movement. His work has been deeply influenced by both jazz and Indian classical music.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/49/Terry_riley.jpg/220px-Terry_riley.jpg
